Update pnginfo.c to fix build failure

Fix build failure with newer compilers and glibc and security flags:
gcc -DPACKAGE_NAME=\"pngtools\" -DPACKAGE_TARNAME=\"pngtools\" -DPACKAGE_VERSION=\"0.4-dev\" -DPACKAGE_STRING=\"pngtools\ 0.4-dev\" -DPACKAGE_BUGREPORT=\"\" -DPACKAGE_URL=\"\" -DPACKAGE=\"pngtools\" -DVERSION=\"0.4-dev\" -DHAVE_STDIO_H=1 -DHAVE_STDLIB_H=1 -DHAVE_STRING_H=1 -DHAVE_INTTYPES_H=1 -DHAVE_STDINT_H=1 -DHAVE_STRINGS_H=1 -DHAVE_SYS_STAT_H=1 -DHAVE_SYS_TYPES_H=1 -DHAVE_UNISTD_H=1 -DSTDC_HEADERS=1 -DHAVE_PNG_H=1 -I.   -Wdate-time -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2  -Werror -c -o pngread.o pngread.c

pnginfo.c:419:33: error: format '%d' expects argument of type 'int', but argument 2 has type 'long unsigned int' [-Werror=format=]
  419 |                     printf ("* %d ", runlen);
      |                                ~^    ~~~~~~
      |                                 |    |
      |                                 int  long unsigned int

commit.message:
Install docbook2man in the CI builds

Also, set the make install destination to a user-controlled directory
instead of the default /usr/local since the CI user doesn't have
permission there.

Update configure.ac to get rid of deprecation warnings

Also, abort if libpng isn't found. The sentinel function used for this
is also changed since the previous one seems to have been switched to
a macro at some point. Since the program didn't actually use the checks
for various header files, these tests were removed.

Build the release man pages using the makefile

Also, improve other constructs in makerelease to be more resilient
against spaces in file names.
Build/install the man pages using the makefile

commit.message:
pnginfo returns random numbers as return code.

pnginfo returns random numbers as return code. No chance to
tell wether it failed or succeeded. Only a few lines need to
be changed.

pnginfo with -d option does not dump full bitmap

Using pnginfo with -d option on PNG file dumps only part of the bitmap.
This happens on any PNG file. Here is a transcript:
$ pnginfo test.png
test.png...
  Image Width: 279 Image Length: 266
  Bitdepth (Bits/Sample): 16
  Channels (Samples/Pixel): 3
  Pixel depth (Pixel Depth): 48
  Colour Type (Photometric Interpretation): RGB
  Image filter: Single row per byte filter
  Interlacing: No interlacing
  Compression Scheme: Deflate method 8, 32k window
  Resolution: 0, 0 (unit unknown)
  FillOrder: msb-to-lsb
  Byte Order: Network (Big Endian)
  Number of text strings: 0 of 0
  Offsets: 0, 0

$ pnginfo -d test.png | sed 's/] /]\n/g' | grep '\[' | wc -l
24738
$

I expect 74214 number in last command, because the number of pixels in
this file is 279 * 266 = 74214.
